products.body_html: The Horse Chestnut trees planted by Alfred Vogel in the Bioforce fields have grown to splendid maturity. Not to be confused with the edible sweet chestnut, the hard, round seeds of the Horse Chestnut, are assiduously gathered each autumn for use in this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Aesculus Horse Chestnut Tincture 50ml

products.body_html: Agnus Castus, the 'Chaste Tree' is actually a shrub with violet flowers. Found in the Mediterranean region, its uses have been recorded since the time of Hippocrates. The tiny reddish brown fruit, which appear in hte summer, are used to create this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Agnus Castus, Chaste Tree Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Avena Sativa (Oats) has been used for centuries as both a food and a remedy. Alfred Vogel knew that when the oats are just breaking into flower and the seeds beginning to form, the plant is richest in its active ingredients. The oats used in this tincture were grown organically and harvested at the time of optimum potency.
products.title: A Vogel Avena Sativa, Oat Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Berberis is best known as a prickly ornamental bush with bitter red berries. The bark from the herb's woody stems is used in this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Berberis Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Bilberry is a small shrub that grows abundantly in mountainous districts. The leaves resemble those of the myrtle, hence its Latin name of Vaccinium myrtillus. The leafy stems are used in this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Bilberry Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Alfred Vogel knew that the most effective way in which to benefit from Centaurium, known to herbalists as a 'stomach bitter' was to take it in liquid form. The organically grown plants used in this remedy are harvested just as they come into flower to create a sharp tasting tincture which Alfred Vogel recommended.
products.title: A Vogel Centaurium, Centaury Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: The deep red fruit of the Hawthorn are amongst the most familiar of hedgerow berries, adding colour to waysides each autumn. Alfred Vogel relished eating the raw 'mealy' berries as a child and later learned of their true usefulness, utilising their pulp in this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Crataegus, Hawthorn Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Alfred Vogel devoted much of his life to the cultivation of herbs known by native people worldwide to have beneficial effects. Working with scientists and local people on a specially created farm in the Kalahari Desert, Vogel have achieved a unique and sustainable organic farming method for Devil's Claw, a herb notoriously difficult to cultivate.
products.title: A Vogel Devil's Claw, Harpagophytum Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Dormeasan is a traditional herbal medicinal product used for the temporary relief of sleep disturbances resulting from mild anxiety. This is based on traditional use only.
products.title: A Vogel Dormeasan Valerian/Hops Oral Drops 50ml

products.body_html: Echinacea purpurea, treasured by Native Americans for its healing powers, flourished in Switzerland thanks to the skill and perseverance of Alfred Vogel. His original plants are the forerunners of the fresh, healthy herbs used to make this tincture, combined with Plantago lanceolata, a familiar meadow plant known to Vogel. Both are grown organically, free from any contaminants.
products.title: A Vogel Echinacea Complex for Children 30ml

products.body_html: Throat lozenges with fresh organically grown echinacea.
products.title: A Vogel Echinacea Lozenges, 30g

products.body_html: Each spray contains the tinctures of fresh Echinacea purpurea* (Purple Coneflower) herb 190mg, fresh Salvia officinalis* (Sage) leaves 95mg and fresh Echinacea purpurea* (Purple Coneflower) root 10mg. Also contains sorbitol, ethanol, soya lecithin, sucrose ester and peppermint oil. Alcohol content 40%v/v * Organically grown
products.title: A Vogel Echinacea Throat Spray, 30ml

products.title: A Vogel Echinaforce Resistance Drops 100ml

products.body_html: Echinacea purpurea, treasured by Native Americans for its healing powers, flourished in Switzerland thanks to the skill and perseverance of naturopath, Alfred Vogel. Today's strong, healthy plants, still organically cultivated and processed in the most natural way possible, are direct descendants of this original stock and provide the same wide spectrum of effective ingredients.
products.title: A Vogel Echinaforce Resistance Tablets, 120 tablets

products.body_html: Eleutherococcus (Siberian Ginseng) is a native of Eastern Asia. Alfred Vogel learned of the value of this herb from local practitioners during his travels in Russia. It is the root of the plant that is used in this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Eleutherococcus, Siberian Ginseng Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: This is the new name for Vogel's golden grass tea. Golden rod tea is a blended herb tea prepared from organically grown and wild crafted herbs. Golden rod is pleasantly relaxing and may be enjoyed throughout the day.
products.title: A Vogel Golden Rod Tea, 25 tea bags

products.body_html: Alfred Vogel prized both Hawthorn and Garlic highly and wrote extensively about both herbs. Garlic's usefulness has been catalogued back to antiquity and it is combined here with the pulp from the deep red fruit of the Hawthorn, one of the most familiar of hedgerow berries, and the beautiful Passiflora plant.
products.title: A Vogel Hawthorn-Garlic Complex, 150 caps

products.body_html: Ivy, the well-known evergreen climber, was held in high esteem among the ancients and has many traditions attached to it. The Greeks regarded it as a symbol of fidelity. To the Greeks, Thyme denoted graceful elegance and its uses were extolled by Virgil and Pliny. Both Ivy and Thyme feature prominently in Alfred Vogel's writings.
products.title: A Vogel Ivy-Thyme Complex, 50ml

products.body_html: The fronds of Giant Kelp forests, which stretch deep into the cold, nutrient-rich water of the Pacific Ocean, provide the basis for these useful tablets which Alfred Vogel featured extensively in his writings.
products.title: A Vogel Kelp Tablets, 240 tablets

products.body_html: This complex brings together seven tropical herbs originating in various areas of the world.  Alfred Vogel discovered this fascinating complex when he worked with Dr Fritz Aichele, a German naturopath.
products.title: A Vogel Luffa Complex Tablets, 120 tablets

products.body_html: This complex brings together seven tropical herbs originating in various areas of the world.  Alfred Vogel discovered this fascinating complex when he worked with Dr Fritz Aichele, a German naturopath.
products.title: A Vogel Luffa Complex Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Luffa Nasal Spray is a preparation made from a combination of herbs.
products.title: A Vogel Luffa Nasal Spray, 20 ml

products.body_html: Sage (Salvia) boasts the enviable reputation of bringing eternal life.  While it can never achieve this objective, the popularity of this strongly scented herb and the capacity for its leaves to display beads of liquid in hot weather is well documented.  Alfred Vogel commended its value in his writings throughout his life.
products.title: A Vogel Menosan Sage Drops

products.body_html: A native of the Americas, Alfred Vogel saw this 'showy flower' in Mexico and Brazil, learning of its uses from the native people.  The plant was brought to Europe in the 17th century as a garden adornment but naturopaths started to use it about 100 years ago. This herb is combined with the fresh young seeds of Avena sativa (Oats) to creat this useful tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Passiflora Complex Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: This familiar meadow plant is one of the most commonly used by herbalists.  Alfred Vogel knew that the effectiveness of Plantago was greatly enhanced by it being cultivated organically, free from any contaminants.  A. Vogel continue to follow this principle in producing this remedy.
products.title: A Vogel Plantago, Lance Leaf Plantain Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Throat lozenges with spruce shoot extract and honey.
products.title: A Vogel Santasapina lozenges, 30g

products.body_html: Saw Palmetto is made from the oily berries of the Saw Palm, which is to be found in the Florida Everglades.  The uses of this dwarf palm were known to the Seminole and it was from these Native Americans that Alfred Vogel learned about the plant during his visit to the USA in the 1950s.  The Saw Palms, which provide the berries for this remedy, are carefully husbanded in their native habitat using an organic protocol and are protected from other pollutants.
products.title: A Vogel Saw Palmetto Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: The majestic European Golden Rod (Solidago virgaurea) and the fresh leaves from the elegant Birch are combined with two invasive but useful weeds, Horsetail and Restharrow, to make this tincture, which Alfred Vogel recommends throughout his writings.
products.title: A Vogel Solidago Complex Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Alfred Vogel loved this age-old herbal remedy, which thrived in his native Switzerland.  His principles required a thriving, sustainable source for our herbs.  Through painstaking research and organic cultivation, our gardeners identified a species of Hypericum high in active agents and resistant to disease, and so helped create the glorious yellow-headed leafy stems, whose tips are used to make this oil
products.title: A Vogel St John's Wort Oil, 100ml, **External Use Only**

products.body_html: Urtica is better known by its common name, the Stinging Nettle, which only too clearly defines the reason for its general unpopularity.  Its usefulness was know as far back as Roman times and Alfred Vogel encouraged its growth within his fields.  Today our gardeners carefully nurture their crop and twice each year harvest the fresh plant tops for used in this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Urtica, Stinging Nettle Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Alfred Vogel used to create Urticalcin by hand, mixing the ingredients to the correct consistency before hand-pressing the tablets.  The demand was such that he soon had to develop a machine to carry out this laborious task for him while maintaining the quality of this most useful mixture.
products.title: A Vogel Urticalcin, 360 tablets

products.body_html: Uva-ursi or Bearberry is a small woody shrub which thrives in the mountains of Alfred Vogel's native Switzerland.  The origin of its name is unclear but it is suggested that bears may have eaten the fruit with relish.  The herb is first mentioned in 13th century texts and it found a place in all the traditional herbal reference works and in most modern Pharmacopoeias.
products.title: A Vogel Uva-Ursi Complex Tincture, 50ml

products.body_html: Valeriana grows in temperate climes worldwide, the European species being Valeriana officinalis.  This unusually flavoured herb was held in such esteem in the Middle Ages that it was know as All Heal.  Each autumn, Alfred Vogel harvested the amazingly hairy roots of his crop, rich in active ingredients, from his organic fields to create this tincture.
products.title: A Vogel Valeriana, Valerian Tincture, 50ml
